# Support Matrix

| Component | Supported |
|---|---|
| OS | macOS 13+ (BSD tools); Linux with GNU coreutils |
| Shell | `bash` 4+ (declare via `#!/usr/bin/env bash`) |
| Python | 3.10+ |
| `gh` CLI | 2.40+ (only when `--with-github` is set) |
| `git` | 2.30+ |
| Cursor | 1.x with MCP support |

## Notes

- BSD `sed` and GNU `sed` differ for in-place edits; the launcher avoids
  in-place edits and prefers Python helpers where portability matters.
- Lock file uses PID liveness check via `kill -0`, which is portable across
  macOS and Linux.
